THREE
        <div class="container content-banner banner-4">
    <div class="row">
        <div class="col-12 col-md-7">
            <h1>How to discuss hearing loss with a family member or friend</h1>
            <p>Hearing loss can be a senstive subject. Open communication is key to making sure everyone feels respected, understood and cared for. When you have a conversation, here are a few things to remember.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="box-container">

        <div class="box">
        <h2>Explanation is important</h2>
        <p>Hearing loss is difficult to understood for people who haven't experienced it, so it can be helpful for symptoms to be explained.</p>
        </div>

         <div class="box">
         <h2>Emotions should be shared</h2>
        <p>Being open about feelings surrounding hearing loss can help bring family relationships closer.</p>
        </div>

         <div class="box">
         <h2>Stigma needs to be broken</h2>
        <p>When hearing loss is treated as a regular part of the family dynamic, people will become more comfortable talking about it.</p>
        </div>

         <div class="box">
         <h2>A sense of humor doesn't hurt</h2>
        <p>Miscommunication happens, but sometimes using humor can lighten the subject.</p>
        </div>
            
        </div>
    </div>
</div>

FOUR
        <div class="container content-banner banner-1 mt-6">
    <div class="row">
        <div class="col-12 col-md-7">
            <h1>Tips for a better conversation about hearing loss</h1>
            <p>Talking to someone with hearing loss may feel overwhelming or frustrating. To have a clearer, more approachable conversation, here are a few tips on what to do - and not to do.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="container">

        <div class="box">
        <picture><img class="heart" src="${URLUtils.staticURL('/images/heart.png')}"
                        alt="hero banner image"></picture><h3>Do</h3>
        <ul>
        <li>Get their attention before speaking</li>
        <li>Face the person while speaking</li>
        <li>Limit background noise</li>
        <li>Keep your hands away from your face</li>
        <li>Speak naturally</li>
        <li>Rephrase rather than repeat misundertood communication</li>
        <li>Use an app that translates spoken words into written words (if needed)</li>
        <li>Create visual signals</li>
        </ul>
        </div>

        <div class="box">
        <picture><img class="heart" src="${URLUtils.staticURL('/images/urgent.png')}"
                        alt="hero banner image"></picture><h3>Do not</h3>
        <ul>
        <li>Tell the person to turn their hearing aids up</li>
        <li>Say "never mind" or "I'll tell you later"</li>
        <li>Be impatient or frustrated with the person</li>
        <li>Assume the person knows sign language</li>
        <li>Ask questions or start a conversation from another room</li>
        </ul>
        </div>
            
        </div>
    </div>
</div>

